1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:36,360
Bege.

3
00:01:37,450 --> 00:01:41,120
I have no interest in assassinating Big Mom.

4
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:45,790
But is she really the type of person
we can kill with guns and cannons?

5
00:01:50,220 --> 00:01:53,880
From what I've heard, she's like an iron balloon.

6
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:56,090
I feel like this is going to be impossible.

7
00:01:56,090 --> 00:02:01,990
Yeah, if we're going to do this assassination,
it has to be done in one blow.

8
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:04,850
Otherwise, we'll be caught in a siege and get killed.

9
00:02:05,740 --> 00:02:08,380
Is an emperor really as strong as they say?

10
00:02:08,380 --> 00:02:10,270
Definitely! She's a monster!

11
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:16,580
When we tried to retrieve Brook, she was fast asleep.
But I still thought we were goners!

12
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:23,030
She killed her own son for the sake of sweets.

13
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:27,980
On that note, why did you choose the tea party,
—where all of her top officers will be in attendance—

14
00:02:27,980 --> 00:02:31,280
as the assassination location, Bege-san ?

15
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:36,010
Well, I knew you guys would ask that...

16
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:40,070
First of all, let me explain something.

17
00:02:40,070 --> 00:02:45,680
Under exact conditions, we'll only need
five seconds to kill Big Mom!

18
00:02:46,570 --> 00:02:48,230
Only five seconds?!

19
00:02:48,230 --> 00:02:50,360
It's not only five seconds-rero !

20
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:55,190
It's won't be that easy to create
that five second opening at the party-rero.

21
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:59,380
The Big Mom Pirates comprises
a bunch of skilled fighters, and they'll all be there.

22
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:05,330
Within a split second, monsters like
the sweet commanders will attempt to stop us-rero !

23
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:11,470
At that point, it'll be a head-on fight, and we have no chance of winning that!

24
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:20,050
This assassination plot began
with the capture of Caesar.

25
00:03:20,050 --> 00:03:24,850
My name is Gastino!
Don't ever call me that in front of Big Mom!

26
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:26,140
Listen!

27
00:03:26,140 --> 00:03:30,990
When this mission is over,
you'll give me back my heart and free me!

28
00:03:30,990 --> 00:03:32,810
That's what we agreed to!

29
00:03:32,810 --> 00:03:34,650
Don't forget that.

30
00:03:34,650 --> 00:03:40,500
If you break your promise,
I'll personally murder your son.

31
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:47,790
Don't get paranoid now, Gas-hiko!
Bege will keep his word!

32
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:50,080
Gas-hiko?! No, it's Gastino!

33
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:52,540
Gas-hiko!

34
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:54,420
You little...!

35
00:03:54,420 --> 00:03:58,880
Who cares what your name is?
You're still a scumbag.

36
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:03,760
Anyway, he's got a very crucial job.

37
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:05,770
That's right!

38
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:09,810
Let me show you what I made!

39
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:14,000
Deadly poison gas: KX launchers!

40
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,900
One will do the job,
but I've got two extra, just in case!

41
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:21,900
Each of them can inject five grams
of deadly organophosphate gas...

42
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:25,460
d-directly into your body!

43
00:04:25,460 --> 00:04:30,120
It's the most audaciously sinful
murder weapon in history!

44
00:04:31,450 --> 00:04:36,360
The gas will destroy an average human
by just touching their skin.

45
00:04:37,460 --> 00:04:41,140
So if it's injected directly into your body...

46
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,970
I'm 100 percent sure...

47
00:04:45,970 --> 00:04:47,890
No, 200 percent sure that you'll...

48
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,430
die!

49
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:52,850
You're definitely gonna die!

50
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:56,560
Everyone will die!

51
00:04:57,140 --> 00:04:59,750
Okay, I get the picture.

52
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:03,360
So you have a weapon
that will kill her if it hits her?

53
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:06,000
No, unfortunately,

54
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,880
if Big Mom is at full strength,

55
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:13,160
this weapon won't be able to pierce through her skin.

56
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:19,290
There aren't that many weapons in this world
that'll work against Big Mom!

57
00:05:26,050 --> 00:05:28,430
Then it's pointless to have that thing!

58
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:30,660
You gotta look at the big picture.

59
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:34,350
I said it wouldn't work when she's at full strength.

60
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:40,250
There are two conditions necessary
to ensure the KX launcher does the job properly!

61
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:45,370
First we need a five-second window
where no one is able to attack us.

62
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:49,780
Secondly, Mama's body has to be weakened somehow.

63
00:05:49,780 --> 00:05:52,620
What kind of convenient situation is that?

64
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,670
What are you doing?!

65
00:05:57,670 --> 00:06:01,800
There is one place where
 all those conditions will be met...

66
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,470
That's the tea party!

67
00:06:08,010 --> 00:06:09,970
Oh, Pez!

68
00:06:14,850 --> 00:06:19,310
I'm sorry! Your daddy-waddy was too loud!

69
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:20,770
It's okay, it's okay!

70
00:06:21,890 --> 00:06:26,150
We've been allied with Mummzie-wumzies
for about a year now...

71
00:06:26,150 --> 00:06:28,360
Um, but we've never seen her get hurt.

72
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,450
Even when she destroyed the city...

73
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,870
Even when bullets...

74
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:43,420
or bombshells hit her...

75
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,510
Even when she sinks a ship...

76
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:57,310
We never saw her get a single scratch on her body.

77
00:06:59,020 --> 00:07:02,810
As you said, she's just like an iron balloon.

78
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,690
But...

79
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:13,030
there was one time
I saw Mummzie-wumzie get a scratch.

80
00:07:14,050 --> 00:07:17,330
The Mother Carmel Picture Incident-rero !

81
00:07:17,330 --> 00:07:19,390
That's right.

82
00:07:21,970 --> 00:07:27,800
At tea parties, there's always a picture placed
directly in front of Mama,

83
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:31,010
and nobody else sits there.

84
00:07:31,010 --> 00:07:35,440
It's one of her most prized treasures.

85
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:37,930
A picture?

86
00:07:37,930 --> 00:07:39,270
Yes.

87
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:42,700
It's a portrait of Mother Carmel!

88
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:45,650
You could say that it's Mama's only weak point!

89
00:07:49,330 --> 00:07:51,530
Who is that person?

90
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:55,370
It seems like Mama is indebted to her,
but we don't know the details.

91
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:57,380
She's a figure of mystery.

92
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:58,990
Is she dead?

93
00:07:58,990 --> 00:08:01,250
I heard she disappeared.

94
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03,870
So she's a missing person.

95
00:08:03,870 --> 00:08:08,020
Even those in the family don't know the specifics.

96
00:08:10,230 --> 00:08:16,400
One time at a tea party, one of the servants
accidentally knocked it off of the table.

97
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,030
Mother...

98
00:08:32,570 --> 00:08:36,070
I was stunned by Mama's reaction to it.

99
00:08:36,070 --> 00:08:41,620
She turned pale and let out
a loud shriek that I'd never heard before!

100
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:47,200
It was different from her ravenous rampage!

101
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:52,720
All we could do was just
 cover our ears to protect our eardrums...

102
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:57,350
People were passing out
and collapsing one after another!

103
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:04,520
On top of the shriek,
she unleashed her conqueror's haki!

104
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:08,150
All because of a jostled picture.

105
00:09:09,370 --> 00:09:11,940
The point is what happened next.

106
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:22,700
Mama knelt down from shock and, believe it or not,

107
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:26,650
she scraped her knee and it was bleeding!

108
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:32,860
I was surprised because I didn't think
she had red blood flowing through her veins.

109
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:38,970
When she breaks down like that,
her body becomes fragile.

110
00:09:38,970 --> 00:09:46,890
So, at the tea party today, if we break that picture
in half, what do you think will happen?

111
00:09:51,910 --> 00:09:53,860
Mama will be devastated!

112
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:58,820
And no one there will be able to move
for more than five seconds.

113
00:09:58,820 --> 00:10:02,740
Then, the KX launcher
 will show its real strength...

114
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:11,170
and Emperor Big Mom will die!

115
00:10:12,690 --> 00:10:17,420
The news of the assassination of Big Mom
will spread across the world!

116
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:21,100
But isn't that shriek gonna
paralyze us, too?

117
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:25,160
Don't worry. We have these.

118
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:28,560
Invisible Symphonia System!

119
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:30,240
Oh, earplugs!

120
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:34,190
If breaking that picture creates such a big mess...

121
00:10:34,190 --> 00:10:37,400
Then we gotta save Sanji's family
during that time, too.

122
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:41,320
Hey, don't act like it'll be that easy.

123
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:46,680
It'll take three seconds for Mama
to freak out after the picture is broken.

124
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:51,920
If you're surrounded by the angry
Big Mom Pirates before it gets messy,

125
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:55,840
it'll be miraculous for you
to stay alive for three seconds!

126
00:10:55,840 --> 00:11:00,260
I need you to take that role, Straw Hat!

127
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:04,020
Wait a minute!
That means Luffy is going to be bait!

128
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:07,430
Bege! Nami and her friends saved Lola!

129
00:11:07,430 --> 00:11:09,810
How could you ask him to be a sacrifice?!

130
00:11:10,530 --> 00:11:11,570
Okay!

131
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,520
I'll do it!

132
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,380
What?!

133
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:27,950
You need to think twice about this...

134
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:33,400
Well, I just came up with an awesome way
to arrive at the party.

135
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:37,810
A way to show up?

136
00:11:37,810 --> 00:11:42,110
What?! What is it?
Sounds like fun! I wanna hear it!

137
00:11:42,110 --> 00:11:43,160
Me too!

138
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,900
No way. If I tell you now, it'll ruin the fun.

139
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:47,390
What?!

140
00:11:47,390 --> 00:11:50,020
– What was I worried for?
– What was I worried for?

141
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:52,850
Sounds good. Then, I'll be counting on you.

142
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,190
Sure!

143
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:58,400
Now, do you know when to break the picture?

144
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:01,040
When Sanji kisses Pudding, right?

145
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:03,350
Idiot, I won't do that! I can't!

146
00:12:03,350 --> 00:12:07,740
The wedding kiss
will draw everyone's attention away.

147
00:12:07,740 --> 00:12:11,290
That's precisely when...

148
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:16,460
Pudding-san will shoot Sanji-san !

149
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:19,200
I'll dodge her shot.

150
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:21,760
The gunshot will be the cue.

151
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:23,890
Okay! Sounds easy!

152
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:27,510
Alright, let's go over the plan.

153
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:34,690
When Pudding shoots,
Straw Hat will break the picture!

154
00:12:34,690 --> 00:12:37,900
Big Mom will start to shriek,

155
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:43,780
and we'll put the Invisible Symphonia System in our ears.

156
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:44,990
Say "earplugs."

157
00:12:44,990 --> 00:12:47,660
Then, it'll be downhill from there.

158
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:52,710
While the partygoers are in a panic,
you guys will rescue Germa.

159
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:57,170
And with the KX launcher
and the deadly poison gas shell,

160
00:12:58,790 --> 00:13:00,700
we'll assassinate Big Mom.

161
00:13:01,510 --> 00:13:04,510
This all needs to be finished in 10 seconds.

162
00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:07,400
As soon as we kill Big Mom,

163
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:09,260
this idiot will arrive.

164
00:13:09,260 --> 00:13:10,960
Yes, that's when I'll arrive!

165
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:13,350
Who are you calling an "idiot"?!

166
00:13:13,350 --> 00:13:17,190
– He's such a piece of crap.
– Is this jerk part of the plan?

167
00:13:17,190 --> 00:13:18,400
Shut up!

168
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:24,820
Listen, since I can fly,
I'll plunge on to the site with a mirror to escape!

169
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:27,090
Along with this woman!

170
00:13:27,090 --> 00:13:31,370
I'm not part of this! Mama's gonna kill me!

171
00:13:31,370 --> 00:13:35,550
You guys did a great job bringing Brûlée here.

172
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:39,430
We couldn't have hoped for a more
useful power to help us escape.

173
00:13:40,540 --> 00:13:44,080
Your compliment doesn't
make me happy, you bastard!

174
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:45,880
You bastard!

175
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:50,900
Once you finish,
dive into Caesar's mirror quickly!

176
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:54,640
Big Mom will still be shrieking.

177
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:58,850
And then, we can just run away
in the mirror dimension at our own pace.

178
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:05,070
The mirror will provide you
the quickest way to escape from the island.

179
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:09,070
Through the Mirro-world,
we can get to the Sunny in no time.

180
00:14:09,070 --> 00:14:11,650
That's quite a plan.

181
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:13,740
Yeah, I think it's gonna work well!

182
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:16,880
These bastards...!

183
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:21,580
Once each of us gets to our own ships,
our alliance is over.

184
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:25,210
We should just get out of this territory
as fast as we can.

185
00:14:25,210 --> 00:14:26,910
Good luck in battle!

186
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:29,740
Alright!

187
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:33,240
I guess we're set.

188
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:36,030
The party starts at 10:00, right?

189
00:14:37,780 --> 00:14:40,150
Two and a half hours to go...

190
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:44,270
I gotta go back to my room, since I'm the groom.

191
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:49,180
We have to go back, too.
Let's get ready for fake security duty.

192
00:14:50,820 --> 00:14:54,140
Hey, Bege. Could you do me a favor?

193
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:55,160
What is it?

194
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:57,300
When I show up in a funny way...

195
00:14:57,300 --> 00:15:00,900
Don't try to be funny! You're gonna die!

196
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,800
Today is a holiday because of the tea party!

197
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:09,260
Let's celebrate with Supreme cheese and beer!

198
00:15:09,260 --> 00:15:11,690
So, Madam Pudding's old enough to get married now.

199
00:15:11,690 --> 00:15:16,720
The groom is Germa 66's third son.
We'll have a strong ally!

200
00:15:17,820 --> 00:15:20,790
I heard the whole Du Feld Conglomerate has arrived.

201
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:23,860
A lot of prestigious guests are going to be there today.

202
00:15:24,820 --> 00:15:26,400
Congratulations!

203
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,900
You're celebrating too early!

204
00:15:29,810 --> 00:15:31,450
That's okay! I'm so happy!

205
00:15:32,530 --> 00:15:35,120
Today's Prince Sanji's wedding.

206
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:39,120
The escort soldiers weren't allowed to enter the castle.

207
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:41,810
Obviously, we can't attend either.

208
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:45,980
Of course not. No one needs a guard for a wedding.

209
00:15:45,980 --> 00:15:48,380
Yeah, it should be a peaceful day.

210
00:15:51,970 --> 00:15:56,310
Everyone from the Vinsmoke family,
good morning!

211
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,350
Yonji!

212
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:00,200
Wake up and change!

213
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:03,580
Where's Reiju? She's not in her room.

214
00:16:03,580 --> 00:16:07,230
Oh yeah, I haven't seen her since yesterday.

215
00:16:07,230 --> 00:16:12,710
Oh, Lady Reiju finished with her preparations
in another room.

216
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:13,750
I see.

217
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:19,160
There is still an hour
before the tea party, so take your time.

218
00:16:21,830 --> 00:16:23,990
W-What happened?!

219
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:27,130
Call the ministers!

220
00:16:31,050 --> 00:16:35,510
I-It's not moving! It's dead!

221
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:38,850
My cute little skeleton!

222
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:45,770
That's too bad, but Mama...!

223
00:16:45,770 --> 00:16:49,400
Today is the tea party that you've been waiting for.

224
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:52,070
And what else?

225
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:59,510
♪ The wedding cake! ♪

226
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:11,920
Mr. Morgans and all the other VIPs
have already arrived.

227
00:17:21,850 --> 00:17:26,190
You can't do this to me!
Untie me!

228
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:29,610
We'll leave some water and food.

229
00:17:29,610 --> 00:17:32,730
I'm sorry, but I'm sure someone'll find you soon.

230
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:34,110
Screw you!

231
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:37,740
Where are you guys going?!

232
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:40,410
We're leaving this country.

233
00:17:39,410 --> 00:17:40,410
What?!

234
00:17:40,410 --> 00:17:45,080
That's why you guys were
carrying out your stuff all night long...

235
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,820
Goodbye.

236
00:17:48,790 --> 00:17:54,140
You guys are affiliates of the Big Mom Pirates,
and you're leaving the country...

237
00:17:54,140 --> 00:17:56,340
That means you're betraying Mama!

238
00:17:57,060 --> 00:17:59,140
Does she know about this?!

239
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:01,760
We can't let her find out.

240
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:04,350
She'll kill those who leave.

241
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:06,770
That's what she does, right?

242
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:11,610
Jinbe told us to say thanks.

243
00:18:11,610 --> 00:18:13,320
Jinbe did?!

244
00:18:16,780 --> 00:18:20,700
We're very lucky to have heard Pekoms' story.

245
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:26,410
I don't think Bege can pull off
his plan to kill Big Mom that easily,

246
00:18:26,410 --> 00:18:30,690
but I can't believe Mama is plotting
to assassinate Germa, too.

247
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:36,470
If Luffy and his crew find out about it,
they'll push themselves to save Sanji.

248
00:18:36,470 --> 00:18:42,180
They'll be in danger, and I can't just
sit back and watch! I've got to help them!

249
00:18:43,430 --> 00:18:46,520
That means I will raise...

250
00:18:47,260 --> 00:18:49,350
a full-fledged rebellion!

251
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:53,120
I will betray Big Mom.

252
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:58,780
To fufill my duty to her,
I tried to tell her that I was leaving.

253
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,450
But I withdrew that request,

254
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:05,290
because of the numbers I saw on the roulette wheel.

255
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:12,080
Those numbers represented the comrades
who would've been victimized along with me!

256
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:16,710
That's why I need you all to escape from here.

257
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,920
The price that Big Mom wanted me to pay

258
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:24,680
was an unreasonable sanction
that was more than taking my life!

259
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:28,100
On the day of the tea party, the hors d'oeuvre ships,

260
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:33,440
interceptors from each island,
 will escort the guests, and security will be relaxed.

261
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:38,630
And if something happens at the tea party,
it'll draw everyone's attention.

262
00:19:38,630 --> 00:19:40,740
So that's your chance to escape!

263
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:44,790
I'm prepared for that.
That won't be a problem. But Jinbe...

264
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:50,620
All we want to do is ensure that you can be free.

265
00:19:50,620 --> 00:19:53,000
Yes, I know.

266
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,480
No, you don't!

267
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:58,420
In order to save Straw Hat,
you'd sacrifice your own life!

268
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:04,640
Let's say I join the Straw Hats one day...

269
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:13,910
I will be fighting for my captain, Straw Hat Luffy,
 with my own life on the line!

270
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:16,980
Aladine, it's just a matter of...

271
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:20,570
doing it now or later.

272
00:20:21,550 --> 00:20:24,360
I see. Do as you like.

273
00:20:24,910 --> 00:20:29,500
But do your best to save your own life too.

274
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,700
Okay?

275
00:20:31,790 --> 00:20:34,420
We'll set sail for Fishman Island.

276
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:39,960
You're worried about the Ryugu Kingdom too, right?

277
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:42,130
Yes.

278
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:45,550
We'll protect it no matter what!

279
00:20:49,890 --> 00:20:51,560
I'm sorry!

280
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:54,440
Don't apologize!
We've known each other for decades.

281
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:57,900
We'll live to see each other again, Jinbe!

282
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:09,330
Why would Jinbe feel the need to thank me?

283
00:21:09,330 --> 00:21:11,290
By the way, did he tell Mama...

284
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:13,650
Hurry up and get ready to leave!

285
00:21:13,650 --> 00:21:15,170
Yeah!

286
00:21:15,170 --> 00:21:18,710
Hey, wait! You bastards!

287
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:23,160
Where were you, Reiju?

288
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:24,720
It's none of your business.

289
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:29,370
I know you guys were partying the whole night.
So that's why I asked for a quieter room.

290
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:32,350
Give a grown woman her privacy, you idiot.

291
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:39,270
Let's go. The tea party will take place on the roof.

292
00:21:39,270 --> 00:21:47,320
At last, Germa 66 will have
Big Mom's power on our side

293
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:50,490
and will rule the North Blue again!

294
00:21:50,490 --> 00:21:52,450
You're in a good mood.

295
00:21:52,450 --> 00:21:55,910
But most importantly... Hey!

296
00:21:55,910 --> 00:21:58,230
Sanji hasn't run away, has he?

297
00:21:58,230 --> 00:22:01,920
Both the groom and the bride are fully prepared.

298
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:06,180
What are you thinking, Sanji?
Why didn't you escape?

299
00:22:06,180 --> 00:22:09,340
You know what's going to happen.

300
00:22:13,410 --> 00:22:14,980
I'm depressed.

301
00:22:14,980 --> 00:22:16,270
What's wrong?

302
00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:17,940
Are you nervous?

303
00:22:17,940 --> 00:22:20,230
I don't think so!

304
00:22:22,740 --> 00:22:26,700
I don't want to get any blood on me
after I kill that dumb Sanji.

305
00:22:28,510 --> 00:22:33,490
And in order for everyone to continue to see me
as a good girl, I'll have to erase all their memories.

306
00:22:35,340 --> 00:22:37,520
When I think about all that...

307
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:41,130
it sounds like a pain in the ass!

308
00:22:46,950 --> 00:22:49,640
Everyone has their own objectives...

309
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:54,440
and the tea party from hell will start soon!

310
00:23:18,370 --> 00:23:20,750
♪ It's gonna start! ♪

311
00:23:19,660 --> 00:23:20,750
♪ It's gonna start! ♪

312
00:23:20,750 --> 00:23:26,130
♪ It's time for Mama's tea party! ♪

313
00:23:26,130 --> 00:23:28,170
♪ It's time! ♪

314
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:32,340
♪ It's time! ♪

315
00:23:28,170 --> 00:23:32,340
♪ It's time! ♪

316
00:23:34,690 --> 00:23:38,310
♪ A porkswagon comes a-rushing! ♪

317
00:23:38,310 --> 00:23:40,560
♪ I wonder if he can make it... ♪

318
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:44,770
♪ He's late! ♪

319
00:23:42,310 --> 00:23:44,770
♪ He has to hurry! ♪

320
00:23:44,770 --> 00:23:50,070
♪ The big guests ♪

321
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:54,070
♪ will come out! ♪

322
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:25,110
♪ Why did you get invited, undertaker? ♪

323
00:25:25,110 --> 00:25:27,500
♪ You're so small-minded; stop it ♪

324
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:28,570
Lady Stussy!

325
00:25:28,570 --> 00:25:32,090
♪ Can't an undertaker celebrate
people's weddings? ♪

326
00:25:33,220 --> 00:25:39,350
♪ I won't have anyone who smells so much like blood
talking crap about me, Du Feld! ♪

327
00:25:39,350 --> 00:25:45,020
♪ Hey, I'm so happy to be invited ♪

328
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:47,310
President Morgans!

329
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:52,460
♪ This marriage will be big news!
Germa and our company are strongly tied ♪

330
00:25:53,070 --> 00:25:58,120
♪ But it's a story that has already been
spread across the underworld ♪

331
00:25:58,120 --> 00:26:00,570
♪ So it's too old! ♪

332
00:25:58,990 --> 00:26:00,570
♪ That's right, that's right ♪

333
00:26:00,570 --> 00:26:04,000
♪ It doesn't need to be transported ♪

334
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:08,960
♪ Hi there, how are you? Welcome! ♪

335
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:10,540
Perospero-kun !

336
00:26:10,540 --> 00:26:14,920
♪ Kingpins of the underworld, ♪

337
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:18,010
♪ if you walk through the castle
you're going to be a little late! ♪

338
00:26:18,010 --> 00:26:20,010
♪ Would you like me to... Lick... ♪

339
00:26:20,010 --> 00:26:23,390
♪ take you there? ♪

340
00:26:29,860 --> 00:26:30,860
Wow!

341
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:53,960
♪ By the candy escalator! ♪

342
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:07,230
– This is amazing!
– His candy sculptures are always...

343
00:27:07,230 --> 00:27:12,150
♪ ...a true work of art! ♪

344
00:27:13,270 --> 00:27:15,820
I'm humbled.

345
00:27:16,340 --> 00:27:19,260
Mama hates late arrivals.

346
00:27:19,260 --> 00:27:22,160
So, shall we?

347
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:26,620
Oh, the staircase is moving!

348
00:27:26,620 --> 00:27:28,570
How beautiful!

349
00:27:28,570 --> 00:27:31,530
This is great. Very easy.

350
00:27:31,530 --> 00:27:33,210
See you later.

351
00:27:35,150 --> 00:27:36,500
You can have these.

352
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:42,640
Wait three minutes
and you can lick the candy escalator.

353
00:27:43,560 --> 00:27:46,680
Now, I've gotta go, too.

354
00:28:07,030 --> 00:28:08,750
It smells good.

355
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:10,460
Please come in.

356
00:28:10,460 --> 00:28:13,540
This place always looks so delicious.

357
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:15,730
Welcome, guests.

358
00:28:15,730 --> 00:28:18,190
Hi, Smoothie.

359
00:28:18,190 --> 00:28:20,630
Would you like a welcoming drink?

360
00:28:20,630 --> 00:28:26,690
Today, we have a little bit of Mount Mauri lava,
a beautiful woman who stabbed a thousand men,

361
00:28:26,690 --> 00:28:30,350
and a giraffe that makes funny sounds.

362
00:28:30,350 --> 00:28:33,160
– l'll have a cup of the giraffe.
– Me too.

363
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:35,150
Okay. I'll squeeze it now.

364
00:28:41,510 --> 00:28:43,450
That's hilarious!

365
00:28:46,450 --> 00:28:48,580
Here you go.

366
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:57,060
It tastes so good. And it's smooth to drink, too.

367
00:28:59,250 --> 00:29:00,800
Open up!

368
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:03,620
I refuse to be searched!

369
00:29:03,620 --> 00:29:06,410
No, you can't do that, Mr. Jigra.

370
00:29:06,410 --> 00:29:08,030
Let go of me!

371
00:29:08,030 --> 00:29:11,300
I said let go of me!

372
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:20,480
Is Big Mom already inside?

373
00:29:21,610 --> 00:29:26,540
See, I had an invitation from the last tea party.

374
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:30,580
But sadly, I was unable to be here.

375
00:29:30,580 --> 00:29:34,160
I had to attend my mother's funeral!

376
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:36,920
I wrote my reasons in a letter,

377
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:41,300
but guess what Big Mom sent me in response!

378
00:29:45,170 --> 00:29:48,010
It was my hospitalized father's...

379
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:10,620
Hey! Who shot?! He's a guest!

380
00:30:15,150 --> 00:30:16,320
You are...

381
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:36,560
Sweet Commander Katakuri!

382
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:41,770
Why did you shoot him?!

383
00:30:41,770 --> 00:30:44,530
This is what he was going to say:

384
00:30:45,130 --> 00:30:49,880
"...but guess what Big Mom sent me in response!"

385
00:30:50,490 --> 00:30:53,990
"It was my hospitalized father's head."

386
00:30:54,990 --> 00:30:58,580
"I'm here today to get revenge."

387
00:30:58,580 --> 00:31:00,710
"Open the gate."

388
00:31:00,710 --> 00:31:01,790
Bang.

389
00:31:02,540 --> 00:31:04,840
Bang, he shot.

390
00:31:05,750 --> 00:31:09,550
Two of your men would've been shot.

391
00:31:11,140 --> 00:31:17,760
Is it wrong for me to throw a jelly bean
at him before that could happen?

392
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:20,080
Rook Bege.

393
00:31:21,930 --> 00:31:25,220
Tell Mama that I made the decision.

394
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,650
This is what you're gonna say now:

395
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:32,270
"I see."

396
00:31:32,270 --> 00:31:34,740
"Alright then."

397
00:31:36,820 --> 00:31:40,570
He'll be the biggest pain in the ass at the party.

398
00:31:40,570 --> 00:31:46,190
His observation haki is so good
that he's able to see slightly ahead into the future.

399
00:31:46,190 --> 00:31:48,260
His bounty is over a billion.

400
00:31:48,260 --> 00:31:50,500
He's a monster!

401
00:31:52,060 --> 00:31:54,820
I see. Alright then.

402
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,440
It's about time.

403
00:32:21,910 --> 00:32:25,380
It's time for the tea party.

404
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:37,220
Everyone! Thank you for coming all this way!

405
00:32:46,110 --> 00:32:53,820
Wherever you look, all you see are sweets!

406
00:33:01,790 --> 00:33:02,910
Eat!

407
00:33:04,710 --> 00:33:05,790
Drink!

408
00:33:07,540 --> 00:33:13,430
And enjoy the party to your heart's content!

409
00:33:14,340 --> 00:33:17,470
Enjoy everything...

410
00:33:18,180 --> 00:33:20,580
that'll take place here!

